quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  53,1,By the star when it sets
  53,2,"Your companion [the Prophet] has neither strayed nor is he deluded"
  53,3,Nor does he speak out of his own desire
  53,4,"It is but a revelation sent down [to him]"
  53,5,"He was taught by [an angel of] mighty power"
  53,6,"and of great perfection, who manifested himself [in his true form]"
  53,7,when he was on the higher horizon
  53,8,"Then he approached [the Prophet] and descended"
  53,9,until he was only two bow-lengths away or even closer
  53,10,Then he revealed to His slave what he had to reveal
  53,11,"The [Prophet’s] heart did not deny what he saw"
  53,12,Do you dispute with him concerning what he saw
  53,13,He certainly saw him a second time
  53,14,"at the Lote Tree of the Utmost Boundary [in the seventh heaven]"
  53,15,near which is the Garden of Abode
  53,16,"when the Lote Tree was overwhelmed with [divine] splendors"
  53,17,"His gaze did not wander, nor did it look beyond the limit"
  53,18,He certainly saw some of the greatest signs of his Lord
  53,19,"Have you [O disbelievers] thought about [the idols of] al-Lāt and al-‘Uzzā"
  53,20,"and Manāt, the third one as well"
  53,21,Do you choose for yourselves males and for Him females
  53,22,That is then an unfair division
  53,23,"These [idols] are no more than names you and your forefathers have made up, for which Allah has not sent down any authority. They follow nothing but conjecture and what their souls desire, although there has come to them guidance from their Lord"
  53,24,Is it that man can get whatever he wishes for
  53,25,"Rather, to Allah belongs the Hereafter and this world"
  53,26,How many angels there are in the heavens whose intercession will be of no avail except after Allah’s permission to whom He wills and pleases